      <item>
        <title>Mullvad VPN Install</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[eternity]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote no-group" data-username="komms" data-post="1" data-topic="1650">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://forums.kicksecure.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/919ad9/48.png" class="avatar"> komms:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>add the Mullvad repo</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Optional trick for folks wanting less typing: If you install Mullvad <strong>Browser</strong> using the browser choice GUI (System Maintenance Panel &gt; Install a Browser), it enables the Mullvad repo during the process. Coincidentally, that’s the same repo containing <code>mullvad-vpn</code>, so you can just install that package. (With the “Manage Software” button, the entire process can be done without typing a single command.) Afterwards, you can remove the browser if you want.</p>
<p>This comment is not an endorsement of Mullvad, their browser, or their VPN. It is an endorsement of the handy Kicksecure panel, though. The panel really simplifies a lot of common tasks for folks not familiar with shell. Even for shell experts, it still saves a lot of typing and offsets some productivity loss from having to reboot into sysmaint.</p>
          <p><a href="https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/mullvad-vpn-install/1650/4">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
